  "text": "The consumer offset commit flow in Apache Kafka travels from the client through the group coordinator to the __consumer_offsets topic as follows:\n\nCLIENT SIDE:\n1. KafkaConsumer.commitSync() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/KafkaConsumer.java:1039) - The public API entry point that delegates to the internal consumer implementation.\n\n2. ClassicKafkaConsumer.commitSync() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ClassicKafkaConsumer.java:741) - The internal implementation that validates the commit and calls the coordinator.\n\n3. ConsumerCoordinator.commitOffsetsSync() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ConsumerCoordinator.java:1140) - Handles synchronous offset commits, waiting for completion with retries and timeout management.\n\n4. ConsumerCoordinator.sendOffsetCommitRequest() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ConsumerCoordinator.java:1270) - Creates an OffsetCommitRequest message containing the offsets and metadata for each topic partition, then sends it to the group coordinator broker.\n\nBROKER SIDE - REQUEST HANDLING:\n5. KafkaApis.handleOffsetCommitRequest() (core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/KafkaApis.scala:347) - Receives the OffsetCommitRequest and delegates to the GroupCoordinator to process it.\n\n6. GroupCoordinatorService.commitOffsets() (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorService.java:1971) - The main entry point for offset commits in the group coordinator. This method schedules a write operation on the coordinator runtime.\n\nCOORDINATOR STATE MACHINE:\n7. GroupCoordinatorShard.commitOffset() (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorShard.java:852) - The shard handler that delegates to the OffsetMetadataManager.\n\n8. OffsetMetadataManager.commitOffset() (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/OffsetMetadataManager.java:600) - Validates the offset commit request, creates response data, and generates coordinator records for persistence.\n\nOFFSET LOG PERSISTENCE:\n9. GroupCoordinatorRecordHelpers.newOffsetCommitRecord() (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorRecordHelpers.java:467) - Creates a CoordinatorRecord with OffsetCommitKey and OffsetCommitValue, which represents the offset commit to be persisted.\n\n10. CoordinatorRuntime.scheduleWriteOperation() (coordinator-common/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/common/runtime/CoordinatorRuntime.java) - Schedules the CoordinatorRecords for batched writing to the log.\n\n11. CoordinatorPartitionWriter.append() (core/src/main/scala/kafka/coordinator/group/CoordinatorPartitionWriter.scala:137) - The final step that calls replicaManager.appendRecordsToLeader() to append the serialized records to the __consumer_offsets topic partition.\n\nThe offset records are ultimately persisted in the Kafka __consumer_offsets internal topic with the group ID, topic name, and partition as keys, allowing the consumer group to resume consumption from the committed offset upon restart."
